<HEADLINE> Industrial Sector Booming in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The industrial sector in east
China's Jiangsu Province maintained its momentum this year, with
production-to-sale ratio and economic returns inching up,
according to information released today by the provincial
statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
All state as well as non-state industrial enterprises with
annual sales beyond 5 million yuan each generated a record 77.3
billion yuan in output value in May, rising 13.8 percent compared
to May of 1997 and rising 4 percent from the previous month this
year.
</P>
<P>
Gross Domestic Product (GDP) in Jiangsu Province, one of
China's economic leaders, is expected to grow at 11 percent this
year. Industrial processing is the critical part of local economic
setups, so industrial added value is expected to contribute more
than half of the local GDP this year.
</P>
<P>
Among local industrial products, 34 continued big increases in
output this year, especially notebook computers and
program-controlled exchanges rising more than 100 percent and 67
percent in production over last year, respectively.
</P>
<P>
During the January-May period, the local industrial
production-to-sale rate reached 94.4 percent, 0.1 percent higher
than the same period in 1997. The rate in May of this year hit a
record 95.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the growing industrial output, the slide of
enterprises' economic returns has been checked to some extent, the
report shows.  
</P>
</TEXT>
