<HEADLINE> ECOWAS Sorrow Over Abacha's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Secretary of the
Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS), Lansana
Kouyate, Tuesday expressed his "deep sense of sorrow" at the
sudden death of General Sani Abacha, Head of State of Nigeria and
Chairman of the regional group.
</P>
<P>
In a press release issued here at the on-going three-day
Summit of the Organization of African Unity scheduled to end
Wednesday, the ECOWAS chief expressed his hope that "peace and
stability will continue to be preserved in Nigeria in order to
ensure the harmonious development of the country."
</P>
<P>
Kouyate also paid tribute to the contribution of Abacha on
behalf of the ECOWAS staff, "for his contribution to the
integration efforts in the sub-region."
</P>
<P>
Abacha was said to have died of heart attack in the early
hours of Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
