<HEADLINE> March Supporters, Opponents Clash in Bangladesh City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- At least 50 people were injured
Tuesday during clashes in the southeastern port city of Chittagong
between supporters and opponents of a "long march" staged by
Bangladesh's seven-party opposition alliance, a report reaching
here said.
</P>
<P>
Besides, about 25 vehicles were damaged and several shops
ransacked, the report quoting eyewitnesses as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP)-led opposition started
the two-day long march from Dhaka Tuesday morning toward the
Chittagong Hill Tracts in protest against a peace treaty the
government signed with the tribals last December.
</P>
<P>
As a result of road barricades erected by opponents of the
march and traffic jams, the long marchers could not reach
Chittagong in the evening as scheduled, another report said.
</P>
<P>
They might reach the port city late Tuesday night or early
Wednesday morning, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The march is expected to continue Wednesday morning toward
Khagrachhari, one of the three hill districts, by the major
opposition BNP and toward Rangamati, another hill district, by the
Jammata-e-Islami.
</P>
<P>
The seven-party alliance includes the BNP, the
Jammata-e-Islami, the Jatiya Party, the Democratic League, the
National Democratic Party, the Progressive Nationalist Party and
the Democratic Nationalist Alliance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
