<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Sends Naval Contingent to Help Indonesians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Singapore, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Singapore has sent a naval
contingent to join the Indonesian Navy in carrying out a two-week
social-civil project in a remote area of Indonesia, the Defense
Ministry said in a press release Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The contingent, consisting of some 100 personnel, has embarked
on the project with an assignment to help their Indonesian
counterparts in conducting activities aimed at improving the
living conditions of villagers in the area, the ministry said,
adding that the project is scheduled to last from June 9 to 23.
</P>
<P>
But the ministry did not explain why that area has been chosen.
</P>
<P>
The naval contingent will provide medical, food and educational
assistance to the villagers and improve infrastructure and public
roads there, it said.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry, a landing ship of the Singapore Navy
and two Indonesian naval ships have been sent to take part in the
project and a medical team is along with the naval contingent to
provide basic medical and dental care and conduct medical talks
and screening for the villagers.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time that the Singapore Navy has joined its
Indonesian counterpart in conducting similar activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
