<HEADLINE> Cyclone Hits West Coast of India, Killing 56 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 9 (Xinhua) -- At least 56 people were killed
and more than 50 others injured when a cyclone lashed coastal
areas of West India Tuesday at speeds up to 120 kilometers per
hour, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
The cyclone, caused by a deep depression in the Arabian Sea,
flattened homes and snapped communication links in the coastal
areas of Gujarat and Jalore District of Rajasthan.
</P>
<P>
PTI said the army stationed in the affected areas was alerted
and helicopters were put into service for relief and rescue
operations as the storm felled trees disrupting traffic and cut
off communication links. 
