<HEADLINE> world cup 001 hke-- Scotland Hope to Pull First Upset in World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Underdogs Scotland hope to pull off
the first major upset of the World Cup by beating defending
champions Brazil in the opening match on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held on Tuesday afternoon, Craig Brown,
head coach of the Scottish team, said he hoped to beat Brazil in the
"biggest match" for Scotland.
</P>
<P>
"It will be a big match for us and we hope to achieve a good
result," Brown said.
</P>
<P>
"Of course the Brazilians are favortes, but we are a disciplined
team with many skillful players. I think we could do better than
four years ago at the Foxboro stadium." Brown said.
</P>
<P>
Former England great Sir Bobby Charlton also tipped Scotland to
pull off an upset:"The Brazilians are favored, but there is a lot of
expectation that they will do well and they will be under pressure
in the first game. Brazil need to perform well and the Scots could
capitalise on that." Charlton said.
</P>
<P>
Asked which teams he thought could win the World Cup, Brown
said:"Brazil, Germany, Spain and France." 
</P>
</TEXT>
