<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ruehe: NATO Should Use Force to End Kosovo Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- German Defense Minister Volker Ruehe
said Tuesday that if necessary, NATO should use force to stop
killings in the Serbian province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters in Bonn, Ruehe said he expected a NATO
defense ministers meeting in Brussels Wednesday would make a
clear-cut decision on the Kosovo issue. All military options must
be examined, he added.
</P>
<P>
Ruehe noted Germany would also send troops if NATO decided to
intervene in Kosovo. However, he stressed that any NATO
intervention would require approval by the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
According to the German defense minister, NATO could first
conduct military exercises in Albania and the Repubic of Macedonia
to "send a strong political and military signal" to Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the NATO meeting in Brussels should not just
make a symbolic gesture. At issue was how to stop the war as soon
as possible, Ruehe said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after meeting German Chancellor Helmut Kohl in Bonn
earlier Tuesday, Russian President Boris Yeltsin warned against
any outside military intervention in Kosovo, saying that such an
action would lead to escalation and spread of the conflict to the
whole Balkans.
</P>
<P>
The Russian leader said he would meet with Yugoslav President
Slobodan Milosevic to try to seek peaceful solutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
