<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Calls to Help Injured, Displaced people </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia Tuesday called on
local and foreign humanitarian organizations to provide aid to
people injured and displaced by the present border conflict
between Ethiopia and Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Ethiopian Disaster Prevention and
Preparedness Commission said in addition to those displaced by
the conflict, there are also Ethiopians driven out from Eritrea
after all their properties were confiscated by the Eritrean
forces.
</P>
<P>
The statement said although the Ethiopian government provided
various aids to help war victims and displaced people, the rise
daily in the number of displaced people has necessitated
additional service of assistance.
</P>
<P>
It said local and foreign humanitarian agencies requested to
provide grain, cereal, nutritious food, condiments, clothes,
blankets, tents, plastic sheets, various utensils, water drums
and tankers, jerry-cans, medicines, medical equipment and other
necessary materials.
</P>
<P>
According to the commission, the number of displaced people in
Tigray region now stands at 126,000.
</P>
<P>
An a similar development, the Ethiopian parliament Tuesday
passed a resolution addressed to the international and African
parliaments about the massacre of children and elders by Eritrean
air-raids on June 5, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The resolution said, the parliaments should consider the
brutal act by the invading forces on defenseless children and the
civilians in a similar way to war crimes committed in Rwanda and
Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
