<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Set up New Lab to Check Imported </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Health Minister Aaron
Chiduo said Tuesday that Tanzania plans to set up the National
Drug Quality Control Laboratory.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a parliamentary session in the new capital of
Dodoma, Chiduo said that his ministry is finalizing the
establishment of the laboratory.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the new laboratory, in collaboration with
the Chief Chemist Laboratory, will be responsible for making
thorough investigation into the quality of all drugs to be
imported, according to a report reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Chiduo was answering a question raised by a member of
parliament, Joseph Rwegasira, who wanted to know what steps the
government has taken against companies which import expired
drugs.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that the Ministry of Health has been making
efforts to check the quality of drugs.
</P>
<P>
The ministry in early 1990s banned the Interpham company which
was involved in importing expired drugs, Chiduo said, adding that
since then, no companies have been found to commit similar
offenses. 
</P>
