<HEADLINE> Museveni Mourns Students' Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
Tuesday expressed shock and sorrow over the death of dozens of
students in western Kabarole district who were burnt by rebels in
their dormitories Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
In a message from the State House here, Museveni regretted the
continued lawlessness of elements who are bent on inflicting
suffering on the innocent people, and condemned the act as
inhuman and totally criminal.
</P>
<P>
The president reiterated his determination to crack down on
the rebels of the Allied Democratic Front (ADF) and to bring them
to book.
</P>
<P>
Museveni said that he was deeply sympathetic with the bereaved
families and all those who suffered in the incident.
</P>
<P>
Some 200 to 300 ADF rebels are reported to have launched a
surprise attack on the Kichwamba Technical College at 5:30 a.m.
Monday.
</P>
<P>
They overpowered the security personnel there before setting
students' dormitories on flame.
</P>
<P>
Some 80 students are feared to have been abducted by the ADF
bandits who were cornered by government army and Congolese
soldiers recently.
</P>
<P>
The rebels abducted civilians in western districts and
threatened with terrorism in cities, setting the security force
in Kampala on full alert. 
</P>
