<HEADLINE> France'98 Introduces Curtain-raiser Matches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- France'98 will introduce
"curtain-raiser" matches for the first time in World Cup history,
according to the World Cup organizers.
</P>
<P>
The "curtainer-raiser" matches will be played by youngsters from
France and other countries and regions in all of the World Cup matches
except the opening match and the final.
</P>
<P>
By introducing the matches in the World Cup, The French Organising
Committee aimed at the World Cup to be shared by young people.
</P>
<P>
At 60 of the 64 games, 2,400 eleven- and twelve-year old boys
and girls will play in curtain-raiser games.
</P>
<P>
The two World Cup semi-finals will be preceded by very special
curtain-raiser matches between 4 teams from mainly underprivileged
areas in France, South Africa, Mexico and Brazil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
