<HEADLINE> Helmer, Ziege Miss German Training Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Defender Thomas Helmer and midfielder
Christian Ziege were missing when Germany's World Cup soccer squad
held its training session at the Stade Charles Erhmann in Nice, France
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ziege, who plays with Italy's AC Milan, suffered from a severe bout
of flu and still remained in bed.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to be a regular first choice for the German midfield
at the World Cup finals in France thanks to his speedy dribbling down
the left flank.
</P>
<P>
Bayern Munich's 33-year-old veteran Helmer had just recovered from
a knee injury inflicted in March before pulling a thigh muscle in his
right leg recently.
</P>
<P>
After two hours of treatment by the German team doctors he could
went for a short jog.
</P>
<P>
Germany will meet the United States in its first Group F game in
Paris on June 15. 
</P>
