<HEADLINE> France Ready to Back Military Intervention in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- France has expressed its readiness to
back and join a possible military intervention in the Yugoslav
province of Kosovo by the NATO.
</P>
<P>
French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin Tuesday echoed President
Jacques Chirac's statement made in New York Monday that France
will in principle support such a military action, although it
should be decided by the United Nations Security Council.
</P>
<P>
"France is ready to take its part of all necessary answer to
avoid the repetition of a tragedy which we experienced in former
Yugoslavia," said Jospin when he made a brief visit to Lisbon,
Portugal.
</P>
<P>
