Britain, France, Germany and Italy will meet in Paris Wednesday to
prepare for a ministers' meeting of the six nations on Kosovo to
be held on June 12 in London.
</P>
<P>
They will make proposals of "political and military character"
to the United Nations, said French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine.
</P>
<P>
Britain will present a draft U.N. resolution on solving the
Kosovo crisis, to which France will give its support.
</P>
<P>
"We are in the process of discussing with the British the exact
text," said the foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
Germany has so far expressed reservation over a military option
in Kosovo and prefers to use economic and diplomatic means to
exert pressure, while Russia is also opposed to the use of force.
</P>
