<HEADLINE> Air France to Ensure One Fourths of Flights Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Strike-crippled Air France will
ensure one fourths of the flights from Paris on Wednesday,
announced the air company on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
These schedules will be similar to those of the past few days
and will include three special flights to bring to France the
national football teams of Austria, Scotland and Italy.
</P>
<P>
In Europe, Air France will guarantee flights to London, Lisbon,
Vienna, Birmingham, Newcastle, Southampton, Hanover, Cologne,
Brussels, Florence, Stutgatt, Amsterdam, Edimburg, Helsinki and
Geneva.
</P>
<P>
As for inter-continental lines, Air France will ensure three
flights to New York and one to Mexico, Buenos Aires, Dakar,
Luanda, Libreville and Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
Pilots of Air France have been on strike for 10 days and no
date is fixed for the resumption of talks between pilots and the
management.  
</P>
