<HEADLINE> Jordan Denounces Jewish Settlement Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Jordan's Royal Commission for
Jerusalem Affairs Tuesday denounced the seizure of Palestinian
houses by Jewish settlers and called on the Israeli government to
commit itself to the agreements it has already signed with the
Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
In a statement concerning the Israeli settlers' take-over
of a pair of Palestinian buildings in Arab East Jerusalem on
Monday, the commission said that the Israeli government,
particularly the Western Jerusalem Municipality, was held
responsible for the "illegal act, which undoubtedly proves that
the Israeli settlement program is going ahead under the
government umbrella to complete the judaization of the Holy
city."
</P>
<P>
The statement noted that Israel, through its continued
settlement program in Jerusalem and other areas, "plans to
impose the de facto situation on the Palestinian side when the
final status negotiations begin."
</P>
<P>
Under the Oslo accords and other Palestinian-Israeli
agreements, the issue of Jerusalem will be discussed in the final
status negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The statement finally called on the international community to
exercise further pressure on Israel to honor the U.N. resolutions
and the agreements it signed with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, dozens of armed Jewish settlers moved in the Arab
East Jerusalem and took over five apartments in two buildings in
the Silwan neighborhood adjacent to the Al Aqsa Mosque. At least
two people were injured as the Palestinians clashed with the
settlers. 
</P>
