<HEADLINE> Myanmar Aims at Eliminating Opium Production in 15 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is determined to
achieve its goal of total elimination of poppy growing and opium
production in 15 years, Home Minister Tin Hlaing said here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the on-going U.N. special session on drugs, he said
Myanmar has seized and destroyed over 3,880 kilos of heroin,
24,800 kilos of opium, 11 million tablets of stimulants and burned
down 87 heroin refining camps in the past ten years.
</P>
<P>
In the drug suppression endeavors, 766 members of the Myanmar
Armed Forces have lost their lives and 2,292 others sustained
severe injuries, he said.
</P>
<P>
The drug problem in Myanmar is a legacy of its colonial past
and it was further aggravated after independence with the drug
production and trafficking linked with the internal insurgency
problems, he added.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has been engaged in drug control activities in
cooperation with China and Thailand, and signed bilateral
agreements with India, Bangladesh, Vietnam, Russia, Laos and the
Philippines in this area, the Minister said.
</P>
<P>
He said it is the "moral imperative for the donor community to
play the role of staunch supporter of the efforts against illicit
narcotic crops". 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
