<HEADLINE> LIFFE Members Vote Decisively in Favor Of Board </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Proposals to reform the structure of
the London International Financial Future and Options Exchange
(LIFFE) received overwhelming support from the Exchange's
membership at an Extraordinary General Meeting Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Voting at the meeting represented a 77 percent turnout with 98
percent in favor of the Resolution and 2 percent against,
according to an announcement by LIFFE.
</P>
<P>
The LIFFE's strategy document states that it will develop a new
Automated Trading Platform for financial futures to be introduced
in the second quarter of 1999.
</P>
<P>
LIFFE will also adopt a profit-making objective with a view to
generating value for shareholders and, where appropriate, paying
dividends.
</P>
<P>
The document says the Exchange's corporate structure will be
radically revised to enable non-members to become shareholders in
the Exchange.
</P>
<P>
LIFFE will continue to enhance its open outcry environment
through the greater use of technology, it adds.
</P>
<P>
Jack Wigglesworth, LIFFE's Chairman said: "This vote enables
LIFFE to regain the strategic initiative and to refocus as a
profit-making organization, serving the interests of our members."
</P>
</TEXT>
