<HEADLINE> World Bank Assists Ecuador in Health Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday approved a
45 million U.S. dollar loan for Ecuador's health services
modernization project.
</P>
<P>
This project will assist in expanding access to, and improve
the quality and efficiency of, ambulatory and hospital services,
particularly maternal and child health services.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to develop new decentralized health
care organization, financing, and managerial models in selected
provinces and municipalities.
</P>
<P>
In the medium term, the project is expected to contribute to
the reduction of health disparities in project areas. This
improvement will be attained through improvements in health status
of the poor people who are at the highest risk of premature death,
disease, and disability, gauging progress in terms of declining
mortality in mothers, infants and children under five years old.
</P>
</TEXT>
