<HEADLINE> World Bank Helps Agricultural Research and </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Tuesday a 60 million U.S. dollar interest-free credit to support
agricultural research and training project in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The project will directly benefit Ethiopia's small-scale
farmers, who make up about 85 percent of the total population and
90 percent of agriculture producers.
</P>
<P>
For Ethiopia, the East African country with one of highest
poverty and lowest food security rates in the world, this project
will help promote economic growth, reduce poverty, protect the
environment, and will support the effort to enhance national food
security.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be provided by the International Development
Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessional lending wing for
developing countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
