<HEADLINE> 6 Foreign Demonstrators Arrested in Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Six foreign demonstrators were
arrested on Wednesday in Silwan Village near the Old City of East
Jerusalem in confrontations with Jewish settlers and police.
</P>
<P>
The arrests occurred when about 100 foreign, Palestinian and
Israeli human rights activists held a peaceful demonstration
outside two of the 13 Palestinian houses in Silwan which had been
seized by Israeli settlers.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators, from over 30 countries including the United
States, Canada, Britain and Sweden, expressed their outrage at the
seizure of Palestinan homes by the Jewish settlers.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators are attending a four-day conference in East
Jerusalem on human rights issues of Israel and the Palestinian
territories. The conference was organized by the International
Committee on the Middle East, a mass organization supporting the
Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Four Americans, a French national and a Canadian were arrested
when the demonstration was broken up by Israeli police and
security forces.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators held slogans condemning Israel's human
rights record and urging Israel to observe the 50-year-old
Universal Declaration of Human Rights.
</P>
<P>
When the demonstrators walked down the road leading to another
house which had been seized by the same group of Jewish settlers,
they were met by armed settlers and police, who beat and dragged
away the demonstrators.
</P>
<P>
Several other demonstrators were also injured and one has
been sent to hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration was formerly scheduled to be held in front of
the Israeli Interior Ministry, but the place was changed as the
demonstrators wanted to show their sympathy to the Palestinians
whose houses were seized by Jewish settlers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
