<HEADLINE> Documentary to Be Released on Jiang's U.S. Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A documentary featuring Chinese
President Jiang Zemin's visit to the United States last year has
been made and will be released by the China Film Corp. on June 15.
</P>
<P>
The documentary titled "Crossing the Pacific" was produced by
China Central Television (CCTV) and the Central Newsreels and
Documentary Film Studio.
</P>
<P>
During his eight-day state visit Octover 26-November 2 last
year, President Jiang participated in more than 40 activities and
delivered more than 30 speeches, making extensive contacts with
American people of various social sectors and promoting
Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, another documentary -- "Centennial Ceremony"
on Hong Kong's return to the motherland -- will also be released
at the same time. 
