<HEADLINE> Hit in Chinese Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The ongoing national anti-drug
exhibition, the biggest since the founding of the People's
Republic of China in 1949, has been a hit in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, with the theme "Love life, Reject Drugs," has
attracted more than 140,000 visitors of different ages since it
opened on May 29.
</P>
<P>
This evening, 10 vice-chairmen of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) toured
the exhibition, which cost more than 10 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Siqing, vice chairman of the CPPCC National Committee,
said that the "anti-drug campaign is vital to the future of the
Chinese nation."
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that anti-drug education should be conducted
among young people who are particularly vulnerable to drugs.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Kehui, another vice chairman of the National Committee of the
CPPCC, expressed his hope that the media would spare no efforts in
publicizing the hazards of drugs.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of Public Security, the major sponsor
of the exhibition, a number of visitors to the exhibition have
begun to collect exhibition tickets as souvenirs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
