<HEADLINE> Palestinian Killed Near Jewish Settlement in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A Palestinian was shot dead by
Israeli soldiers near a Jewish settlement in Gaza Strip on Tuesday
night, Israel Radio reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a statement of Israeli Army as saying that
the soldiers opened fire after they found a number of Palestinians
trying to enter the Jewish settlement Morag and killed one of them.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an explosive device was found near the settlement
and the army suspected that it would be used in a terror attack
against Israeli settlers or soldiers, the statement added.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian Police Commander Khaled Abu Oleh was quoted as
saying that the dead Palestinian had been taken to a hospital in
a Palestinian refugee camp about 15 kilometers south of Morag.
</P>
<P>
Oleh noted that the Palestinian and Israeli police were
carrying out a joint investigation over the incident.
</P>
<P>
Israel has handed over most of the Gaza Strip to the
Palestinian National Authority and kept control over the areas
around a number of Jewish settlements.
</P>
<P>
Last month, a number of Palestinians were killed near Jewish
settlements in Gaza when they marked the establishment of the
Jewish state 50 years as a "catastrophe" and clashed with Israeli
troops guarding the settlements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
