<HEADLINE> Trade Union Federation Ends Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The top leader of China's trade
unions today urged all local workers' organizations to guarantee
the basic living standards of laid-off workers and vigorously
carry out the re-employment project.
</P>
<P>
All the trade union organizations across China should listen
to common workers, especially those who have been laid-off, to
hear their views and solve problems for them, Wei Jianxing,
chairman of the Executive Committee of the All-China Federation of
Trade Unions (ACFTU), said at the 19th presidium meeting of the
12th ACFTU Executive Committee.
</P>
<P>
Wei called on the federation and all trade unions to stabilize
China's working class as the country deepens the reform. Leaders
of local trade unions must care for the daily life of the workers
and properly deal with problems among them.
</P>
<P>
The trade unions must firmly make economic development their
central task while safeguarding the legitimate rights and
interests of workers, he said.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, he added, the workers' activity and creativity
should be encouraged and protected by grass-roots trade unions.
</P>
<P>
Participants at the three-day meeting also discussed the work
report of the 13th national congress of the ACFTU.
</P>
<P>
The work of the federation should be guided by Deng Xiaoping
Theory and the guidelines of the 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), said Wei, also a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
The second plenum of the 12th ACFTU Executive Committee defined
the overall principle of the federation. The federation vowed to
seek truth from facts and boldly blaze new trails under the
guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
Wei also encouraged workers to participate in and supervise the
work of the trade unions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
