PARIS -- The striking pilots of Air France and the company's
management have signed an agreement to end the 10-day long strike,
said the biggest pilots union SNPL and the management in a joint
communique Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached hours before the football World Cup
will be officially opened in the Stadium of France and as
criticism against the strikers is rising from both the government
and the opposition.
</P>
<P>
The SNPL, which represents most of the 3,200 pilots of Air
France, asked the pilots to resume flights as soon as possible as
the 10-day long strike is still paralyzing three fourths of the
flights and has already cost the company one billion francs (167
million U.S. dollars). (Air France-Strike-Deal)
</P>
