<HEADLINE> China's Air Force Performs Plateau Aerial Rescue Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Air Force has
successfully conducted an aerial rescue test on the
Qinghai-Tibetan Plateau recently.
</P>
<P>
The test, the first by the Chinese air force on plateaus,
shows that the air force is capable of conducting aerial
rescue operations on plateaus, a senior officer said.
</P>
<P>
The aerial rescue operation includes the self-rescue and
survival of pilots and the rescue operation after pilots
parachuting.
</P>
<P>
As a result, aerial rescue capability is of great importance to
the maintenance of the air force's combat effectiveness and to
civil aviation, rescue operations in disasters and field
explorations.
</P>
<P>
The senior officer said that the test, aiming to examine the
quality of rescue facilities developed by the Chinese air force,
shows that the facilities could help pilots survive three days
after parachuting, making it possible for pilots to wait for the
arrival of rescuers.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the Chinese air force has made successful
rescue tests in jungles, deserts, frigid zones and on the sea.
</P>
</TEXT>
