<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The family of Basorun M.K. Abiola,
the alleged winner of the annulled June 12, 1993 presidential
election who is now in detention, have expressed their sadness
over the death of Nigeria's late head of state, General Sani
Abacha.
</P>
<P>
In a two-page statement issued Tuesday by Abiola's wife,
Mariam, on behalf of the entire family, they also appealed to the
new leader, General Abdusalam Abubakar to take a serious look at
the June 12 issue and immediately free all political detainees
including M.K. Abiola, for a genuine and convincing national
reconciliation.
</P>
