our beloved country and particularly the Abacha family on the
sudden and chocking demise of General Sani Abacha."
</P>
<P>
She said,"Though in detention for the past four
years, I have do doubt that Basorun Abiola will mourn the death
of the former leader."
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Abacha's death on June 8 falls exactly
at the mid-point of the assassination of Abiola's late wife
Kudirat on June 4, 1996 and the June 12 election.
</P>
<P>
The fact, the statement said, is very symbolic and should
serve as the indicator of God's supremacy over man.
</P>
<P>
The family said, "Time has come for the nation to truly move
forward and the only plausible avenue is the free participation
of all Nigerians especially those who are presently detained for
standing by the truth."
</P>
<P>
They implored General Abubakar, "a very modest, urbane and
humane gentleman, to hearken to the voice of reason," saying that
posterity will favor him accordingly.
</P>
<P>
The statement ended with the pray that the Almighty Allah will
grant the Abacha family the fortitude to bear the "irreparable
loss".
</P>
<P>
M.K. Abiola, a billionaire from southwestern Nigeria, was
arrested by the Abacha government on June 24, 1994 in Lagos,
after he declared himself the president of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
His supporters have called for the recognition of the 1993
election after Abacha's death.
</P>
<P>
The new leader, Abubakar said Tuesday night that his
government will adhere to Abacha's transition program, by which
the military is expected to give power to an elected civilian
government on October 1 this year. 
