<HEADLINE> Soybean Program to Provide More Protein to Chinese Youngsters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A nutrition program, the
National Soybean Action Plan, will be carried out nationwide to
improve physical conditions of the Chinese youngsters.
</P>
<P>
An agricultural official said today at a work conference that
tens of millions of people living in rural China lack
sufficient food and clothing, and children in some areas are
suffering from malnutrition.
</P>
<P>
A national survey shows that the amount of protein taken in by
rural children aged 6-12 is lower than that of their
urban counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Partially because of this, the average height and weight of
rural children are also lower than that of children in cities,
the survey claims.
</P>
<P>
Related departments initiated the program in 1996 to spread the
use of soybean-enriched food in hundreds of selected schools in
China's economically backward areas, a nutritionist said.
</P>
<P>
The results proved that foodstuffs made from soybeans have
improved the nutrition of the youngsters, he said, and their
height and weight increased.
</P>
<P>
Eating soybean food is a cheap and effective way to get
enough protein from daily meals, the expert said. "Urban children
can also improve their nutrition system and abnormal
physical conditions such as overweight and emaciation from eating
food made from soybean." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
