Moreover, he said, the further development of friendly
bilateral ties is not only beneficial to both countries but will
be conducive to peace and stability in the region and in Asia as a
whole.
</P>
<P>
Pham Van Tra, also a member of the Political Bureau of the
Vietnamese Communist Party Central Committee, said that Vietnam is
implementing reform and opening-up policy under the leadership of
the Vietnamese Communist Party Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam is benefiting from political stability and economic
growth, and the standards of living of its people has been
improving, he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang congratulated Vietnam on its achievements in carrying out
the policies of reform, opening-up and economic development. He
expressed his belief that the Vietnamese people will make even
greater progress in the cause of comprehensive reform and
socialism-building by pursuing the political line and policies
formulated at the 8th National Congress of the Vietnamese
Communist Party under the leadership of the Vietnamese Communist
Party Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Jiang asked Pham Van Tra to convey his greetings to President
Tran Duc Luong and Le Kha Phieu, general-secretary of the
Vietnamese Communist Party Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Pham Van Tra, at the head of a senior military delegation, said
that most members of his delegation are visiting China for the
first time.
</P>
<P>
The delegation members were deeply impressed by China's
achievements in its modernization drive, he said, adding that the
Vietnamese government and people are pleased to see the growth of
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese armed forces and people are grateful for the
assistance the Chinese government and people have provided in the
past, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the delegation's current China visit
will serve to promote friendship and cooperation between the two
countries and their parties and armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Pham Van Tra conveyed the regards of Tran Duc Luong and Le Kha
Phieu to President Jiang Zemin.  
</P>
</TEXT>
