<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- President Scalfaro's current China
visit will help promote the friendly and cooperative ties between
China and Italy.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Chinese National People's Congress
(NPC) Standing Committee, made the remark during a meeting with
visiting Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro here today.
</P>
<P>
President Scalfaro told Li that he is satisfied with the growth
of bilateral ties and expressed the hope that Italy-China
cooperative relations would be furthered with the joint efforts of
both sides.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China values its ties with Italy and Sino-Italian
relations have witnessed a smooth growth in the past year with
frequent contacts between the leaders of the two countries and
active bilateral cooperation in the fields of economy, trade,
science, technology and culture.
</P>
<P>
Li went on to say that exchanges between NPC and Italian
parliament have been reinforced along with the constant growth of
the two countries' relations.
</P>
<P>
During his predecessor Qiao Shi's visit to Italy last year, he
noted, the leaders of Italian parliament expressed the hope of
enhancing the friendly ties with Chinese NPC. "We quite agree with
the idea, which will help increase our mutual understanding and
establish good relations."
</P>
<P>
Li also briefed the Italian president on the Chinese NPC's
formation and function, as well as its status and role in China's
political life. 
</P>
