<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets Italian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- China and Italy should further
tighten exchanges and cooperation in cultural heritage, Li
Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, said here today.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting Italian President Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro, Li said both China and Italy have ancient civilizations
and have made unique yet important contributions to human
civilization.
</P>
<P>
Rome and the Italian Renaissance have left a far-reaching
impact on world history, he said, adding that Chinese very much
appreciate the Italian people.
</P>
<P>
He said that every ancient country has a task of developing as
well as inheriting its tradition and civilization.
</P>
<P>
The reality is the extension of history, he said, noting that
if development started from historical nihilism and without
heritage, it would lose prerequisites and the foundation, Li said.
</P>
<P>
It also would be difficult to keep the merits and features of
that civilization, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li said the reality is a short period in the long run of
history. Without development and research on the combination with
the times, the traditional culture will lose its vitality and will
not be inherited, he added.
</P>
<P>
"We should follow the development and change of history, apply
modern civilization, means and conditions, make an earnest
research on and sort out the best part of the civilization, and
make a new summary and elaboration to give it a full play," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Li said that, as Italy has many successful experiences in
inheriting and developing its national tradition and culture,
China should learn and draw from it.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro agreed with Li's viewpoints, saying both Italy and
China have ancient civilization and a rich cultural and historical
inheritance.
</P>
<P>
He said both people have done a good job in inheriting and
using these inheritance to serve the happiness of their people and
the future.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the president said, it is very important for the two
nations to strengthen their cultural exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro said his country treasures its exchanges and
cooperation in other fields with China in a bid to keep a
continuous development of the relations between the two
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
