<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close at New Low After Asian Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks plunged 412.09
points, or 4.91 percent, Wednesday to close at 7,979.37, the
lowest since the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The market's turnover was 7,154 million HK dollars (917.18
million U.S. dollars), 3,873 million HK dollars (496.54 million
U.S. dollars) more than that of Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index went down 129.71 points, or 1.55
percent, to open at 8,261.75. It plunged 355.29 points,
or 4.23 percent, to close at 8,036.17 at midday. The share price
then fluctuated around the 8,000-point mark after the market
resumed in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed the loss of the HSI in two straight days to
the negative impact of the weakness of the Japanese yen and higher
interbank interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Index sank 195.17 points, or 2.27 percent, to close at
8,391.46 Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
