<HEADLINE> England Team Arrives in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The English team has arrived in Nantes,
France Tuesday night for the soccer World Cup finals to open in Paris
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation of fifty, with four tonnes of baggage, arrived in
the rain and went straight to their hotel in Saint-Andre-des-Eaux.
</P>
<P>
Nobody made any comment to the press except the head coach Glenn
Hoddle, who said the squad "enjoyed the flight" despite a 30-minute
delay in arrival.
</P>
<P>
This will be England's 10th appearance in the finals and the team,
spearheaded by stars like David Beckham and Alan Shearer, is regarded
as one of favorites to win the cup.
</P>
<P>
England won the tournament only once in 1966, when they played host
to the finals. 
</P>
