<HEADLINE> OAU Describes General Abacha as "True </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) Wednesday said, "General Sani Abacha was a true
pan-Africanist who worked tirelessly for the dignity and security
of the entire continent of Africa."
</P>
<P>
"For years to come, the positive contribution that our late
brother made in ensuring the implementation of ECOWAS and OAU
decisions relating to the restoration of constitutional order and
the re-instatement of the legitimate government of President
Tejan Kabbah in Sierra Leone will be a shining testimony to his
pan-Africanism," said an OAU press release issued here.
</P>
<P>
The release serves as a memorial tribute to the death of
General Abacha, head of state and commander-in-chief of the armed
forces of Nigeria and Chairman of the Economic Community of West
African States (ECOWAS).
</P>
<P>
The press release said that Abacha's boldest initiative had
been the launching in Nigeria of the process of transition aimed
at restoring democratic government to the country.
</P>
<P>
General Abacha "will be remembered for the energy and
resources that he committed towards the restoration of stability
in the west African sub-region."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the OAU appealed to Nigeria's new head of state,
General Abdusalam Abubakar, the government and people of Nigeria
in this tragic and testing time to do all in their power to
maintain peace and security nationwide, strive to achieve
democracy as a nation, and also uphold the unity and integrity of
their great country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
