<HEADLINE> Japanese Department Store Builds Asia Headquarters in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Japanese-funded department store
Jusco has established its Asia headquarters in Hong Kong to
strengthen its Asian operations.
</P>
<P>
Located at Jusco Hong Kong's head office in Quarry Bay, Hong
Kong Island, the new Asia headquarters, which commenced operations
on Wednesday, will enhance support to Jusco stores in Hong Kong,
Malaysia, Thailand, the Chinese mainland and Taiwan in areas of
product merchandising, new store development and human resources
management.
</P>
<P>
Akihito Tanaka, previously managing director of Jusco Hong
Kong, was appointed managing director of the headquarters
and vice chairman of Jusco Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The new set-up will further enhance the department store's
competitive edge in the Asian region, especially under the current
tough operating environment, Tanaka said.
</P>
<P>
"Moreover, we expect the more streamlined communications
channels resulted from the new set-up could facilitate a faster
and more efficient decision making process, which is of great
importance to the business expansion plans of Jusco Hong Kong and
other Jusco operation in Asia," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jusco Hong Kong plans to build a network of 10 chain stores by
the year 2000. Currently it operates six general merchandise
stores in the city, selling a wide range of daily necessity
products. Two more stores are scheduled for opening later this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
