<HEADLINE> A Palestinian Killed in Jewish Settlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 10 (Xinhua) -- An Palestinian was stabbed to
death Wednesday in a Jewish settlement in the West Bank,
apparently by his Jewish co-worker, Israeli police said.
</P>
<P>
The motive of the killing was not yet known, Israel Radio
quoted police spokesman Linda Menuhin as saying.
</P>
<P>
The two men were employed by a Jewish truck driver, who was
delivering soft drinks to the Jewish settlement Maale Efrayim.
</P>
<P>
The driver said he left for a few minutes and when he
returned, he found the Palestinian lying on the floor, bleeding
from a stomach wound. The Jewish co-worker had a knife in his
hand, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Police have detained the driver and the Jewish worker for
questioning.
</P>
<P>
But the names of the dead man and his co-worker were not
immediately made public.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an Arab was slightly injured by stabbing in a
dispute with a Jew in Jerusalem Wednesday. The assailant told
police he was defending himself.
</P>
<P>
In Gaza Strip, a Palestinian was shot dead on Tuesday by
Israeli soldiers guarding a Jewish settlement.
</P>
<P>
Confrontation between Israelis and the Palestinians in the
occupied area have escalated recently after Israel refused to
accept a U.S. proposal to pull back Israeli troops from 13 percent
more of the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli-Palestinian talks have been deeply stranded since
March last year.



10/06/98 12:29 GMT

NNNN
20:40 20:40 g # PAB
</P>
</TEXT>
