<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower across the board Wednesday on
selling activities due to the weakening of the local currency --
the ringgit against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index fell 15.78
points to 489.86, the all-share Emas Index shed 3.26 points to
126.27, the Industrial Index dipped 16.59 points to 972.40, and
the Second Board Index eased 1.30 points to 107.57.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 455 to 114, while 152 counters were
unchanged and 199 counters untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover rose to 111.403 million shares worth 281.603
million ringgit (70.843 million U.S. dollars) from 84.216 million
shares valued at 179.739 million ringgit (45.277 million dollars)
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the main board surged to 104.198 million shares
valued at 271.586 million ringgit (68.323 million dollars) from
Tuesday's 77.732 million shares worth 168.329 million ringgit
(42.346 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the Second Board, turnover increased to 7.205 million shares
worth 10.018 million ringgit (2.52 million dollars) from 6.484
million shares valued at 11.411 million ringgit (2.87 million U.S.
dollars) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals stood at 10.747 million shares valued at
27.738 million ringgit (6.978 million dollars) from Tuesday's
5.186 million shares worth 15.882 million ringgit (3.995 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 4.165
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
6.840 million shares, construction 7.539 million shares,
trading/services 38.284 million shares, infrastructure 2.034
million shares, finance 18.274 million shares, hotels 425,000
shares, properties 14.985 million shares, plantation 3.261 million
shares, mining 671,000 shares, trusts 68,000 shares, closed/fund
79,000 shares, and loans 7.573 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
