<HEADLINE> Jinan Renovates Springs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Jinan city, capital of east China's
Shandong province, has made great efforts to renovate 13 blocked
springs.
</P>
<P>
Jinan, famous for the "city of springs", has 162 springs. But
recent years' urban construction and overuse of underground water
did damages to the springs. By 1997, 16 springs have disappeared
and another 21 ones being blocked.
</P>
<P>
In June 1997, the local government issued a regulation to
protect these springs and set up a special organization to take
the responsibility.
</P>
<P>
A large scale renovation was launched in the meantime. In last
year only, the local government allocated 300,000 yuan to redig
the blocked springs and build protecting facilities around the
springs.
</P>
<P>
According to plan, it will repair another 15 springs this year
with investment of 500,000 yuan and all other blocked ones in
three years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
