<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nationwide Support for Reemployment Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Labor and Employment Bureau of
southwest China's Yunnan Province has recently received 300,000
yuan (about 37,000 US dollars) as the first batch of donation for
the reemployment project.
</P>
<P>
The donation came from an advertisement corporation and it was
the first social donation the bureau received, said Bao Yun,
deputy director of the Labor Department of the provincial
government.
</P>
<P>
China will mobilize all sectors of society to support the
reemployment project, an official with the Ministry of Labor and
Social Security said.
</P>
<P>
The number of laid-off workers from state-owned enterprises has
grown rapidly in recent years, reaching more than 11 million by
the end of last year. Yunnan Province has nearly 200,000 laid-off
workers.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has allocated 20 million yuan for the
project, whose expenses will be shared out equally by the central
government, enterprises and society.
</P>
<P>
It will take about five years for China to complete the
adjustment of personnel structure of state-owned enterprises, said
the official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
