<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Share prices plunged to this
year's lowest level on the Singapore market as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index (STII) crashed by 49.4 points to
close at 1,067.81 points Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the trading session, Shares were lower than the
level on January 12 when it took a hammering to close at a
seven-year low of 1,073.47 points.
</P>
<P>
