<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Abolishes 147 Kinds of Fees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of Finance
and five other departments today jointly released a list of 147
kinds of fees to be canceled immediately in a bid to cut down the
burden on enterprises.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that after the cancellation of these charges, a
total of 12 billion yuan can be alleviated annually as the burden
of enterprises.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Ministry of Finance said that this move
will be beneficial both for promoting state-owned enterprise
reform and standardizing government distribution practices, and it
can also create good conditions for further perfecting the
financial and tax system reform.
</P>
<P>
The listed fees are those imposed by government departments at
various levels without authorization from the State Council or the
Ministry of Finance, including fund, surcharge and special fees.
</P>
<P>
The ministry demanded that no new fees can be charged without
ratification from the State Council or the Ministry of
Finance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
