<HEADLINE> National Congress of Chinese Communist Youth League to Be Convened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Youth League of
China, the world's largest youth organization, will convene its
14th National Congress in Beijing from June 19 to 25, the League's
Central Committee announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of this congress includes hearing and examining a
report by the 13th League Central Committee, revising the League
Constitution, and electing the League's new leadership, the 14th
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,469 delegates are expected to participate in the
congress, which is held once every five years.
</P>
<P>
With an average age of 30.2 years, the deputies are mostly
officials from League organizations at all levels and model youth
from various social sectors, said the League Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1922, the Communist Youth League of China currently
has 68.5 million members aged from 14 to 28 years. The League
subjects itself to the leadership of the Communist Party of
China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
