<HEADLINE> Kuwait Calls for Closer Cooperation with Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait has called for cooperation
with Iran to facilitate the transit of people and cargo between
the two countries while enhancing joint efforts in combating drug
trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Kuwaiti Interior Minister Sheikh Mohammad Khaled
Al-Hamad Al-Sabah made the appeal in talks with his Iranian
counterpart Abdollah Nouri Tuesday, the official news agency IRNA
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sabah said Iranians living in Kuwait have amounted to 62,000
from 40,000 before the Iraqi invasion of Kuwait in 1990 and he has
been authorized by the Kuwaiti leadership to provide necessary
living facilities for them.
</P>
<P>
Al-Sabah also said Kuwait is interested in developing
cooperation with Iran in all fields of common interest.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian minister, on his part, hoped the problems between
the two countries, if any, could be solved through negotiations.
</P>
<P>
He said Iran has adopted a constant positive stand in
supporting Kuwaiti sovereignty in international and regional
forums and is determined to further friendly ties with Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Big strides have been made to consolidate Iran-Kuwait bonds, he
said, stressing that exchange of visits by officials of the two
countries would undoubtedly ensure the protection of national
interests and help solve any possible problems.
</P>
<P>
Sabah arrived here Tuesday for a three-day visit, during which
he and Nouri would also oversee the signing of a string of
agreements on security cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
