<HEADLINE> Ecology of Inner Mongolia Grasslands Deteriorates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The deterioration of the ecology of
Inner Mongolia's vast grasslands in north China is accelerating,
according to Hao Yidong, vice-chairman of the autonomous regional
government.
</P>
<P>
Some 38.7 million hectares of Inner Mongolia's grassland is
degenerating and subject to desertification. The total area is
expanding by some one million hectares annually, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hao said the current speed of grassland construction in the
autonomous region lags behind the speed of degeneration and
desertification, which poses a threat to the environment of north
China.
</P>
<P>
With 90 million hectares of grassland, some 76.5 percent of its
total area, Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region plans to bring
the deterioration under control by 2,000, and by 2,010 the
autonomous region expects a remarkable improvement in its
environment, according to an ambitious plan of the regional
government.
</P>
<P>
The autonomous region plans to build 2 million hectares of
grassland this year, and 350,000 hecyares built by planting
grass.
</P>
<P>
The autonomous regional government has called on local
governments to transform desertified farmland into husbandry bases
and vowed to strike hard at those who illicitly exploit grasslands
for other purposes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
