<HEADLINE> 1.2 Million Zimbabweans in Need of Relief Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Over 1.2 million Zimbabweans has
applied for relief food in the past month, which accounts for 10
percent of the country's 11.8 million population.
</P>
<P>
The Herald daily Wednesday quoted the National Early Warning
Unit as saying that about 427,115 and 858,917 people had by last
month applied for food aid under the drought relief program and
grain loan scheme respectively.
</P>
<P>
The number has since increased as many people failed to
harvest.
</P>
<P>
The latest forecast for maize production this year is about
1.4 million tons, a decrease of nearly 400,000 tons from last
season, showing a 33 percent reduction from last year.
</P>
<P>
"The threat of an El Nino-induced drought prompted a reduction
in the hectarage put under crops in all farming sectors," said
the early warning unit. 
