<HEADLINE> Five Major State Projects in Southern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 10 (Xinhua) -- China has 117 major projects this
year, five of them in Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The 4-billion-U.S.-dollar project at the Ling'ao Nuclear Power
Station, which will have four generators of one million kw each,
is the largest in Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
It is at Ling'ao, east of Shenzhen. Its first phase, with two
generators, will be in operation in July 2002, and the second, in
March of 2003.
</P>
<P>
Another major project is the second phase of the Guangzhou
power station, which will have a generating capacity of 1.2
million kw, the same as the first phase.
</P>
<P>
The other projects are the Pearl River Steelworks, the
electrification of the Wuchang-Guangzhou section of the
Beijing-Guangzhou railway, and the first phase of the Xinsha port
project at Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The 600-million-U.S.-dollar investment in the first phase of
the steelworks, was 36 percent of the total investment. The first
steel plate will be produced in August 1999.
</P>
<P>
The 6.9-billion-yuan railway electrification work will be
completed in 2000.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of Xinsha will add ten 35,000-DWT deep-water
berths, at a cost of 1.65 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
