<HEADLINE> COMESA Summit to Be Held Late This Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Common Market for Eastern and
Southern Africa (COMESA) will hold its annual summit in Kinshasa
late this month, COMESA acting Secretary General J.O. Mwencha has
said.
</P>
<P>
The agenda for the summit has been categorized as follows:
preparation for the launching of a free trade area in the year
2000, setting up of the court of justice, appointment of COMESA
chief executive, expansion of Eastern and Southern Africa Trade
and Development Bank (PTA Bank) and clearing house, and the
integration arrangement in other sectors, Times of Zambia
Wednesday quoted Mwencha as saying here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The PTA Bank will aim at increasing its capital base from 400
million U.S. Dollars to a more realistic figure so that it can
expand role in assisting member countries.
</P>
<P>
Mwencha said the theme of the meeting will focus on
information as a tool for increased trade and investment in
COMESA.
</P>
<P>
The meetings will discuss, among other things, reports in
different sectors namely, agriculture, trade and customs,
industry, energy and environment, transport and communications,
women in business and technical cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The summit will also tackle about issues that help to
propel the common market, such as the draft protocol on the free
movement of persons, labor services, and the membership of Egypt
to COMESA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
