<HEADLINE> Agricultural Activities Become a New Tourist Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Agriculture is a kind of
production, but can also be a way of entertainment.
</P>
<P>
Under the early summer sun at weekends, tourists are flocking
to farms and orchids in Beijing's suburbs, where they grow
vegetables, pick up fruit, and go fishing.
</P>
<P>
Some of them even rent a small plot to grow whatever they
choose, apart from enjoying the fresh air to the full.
</P>
<P>
The computerized greenhouse planting is certainly something
tourists do not want to miss. They can not only appreciate plump
and juicy tomato, cucumber and green pepper grown by means of
modern technology, but also can have a taste of them.
</P>
<P>
One farm in Chaoyang district alone attracts 30,000 tourists
from the city every year.
</P>
<P>
The 66 such agro-tourist centers are specially attractive to
children, since there are education centers built specially for
them to learn agro-knowledge. 
</P>
