<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Western Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.3 on the
open-ended Richter scale jolted western Japan on Wednesday
afternoon, the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damage or casualties and no
tsunami or tidal waves warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred around 4:17 p.m. local time, was
centered about 60 kilometers below northern Wakayama Prefecture,
the Japanese government agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
