<HEADLINE> Seven Killed at Bridge Construction Site in Western Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Seven workers were killed and one
seriously injured Wednesday when an iron girder fell on them at a
construction site in Ehime Prefecture, of western Japan.
</P>
<P>
The workers were building a bridge as part of an expressway
that connects Japan's main island of Honshu and Shikoku, the
country's fourth largest island, said a Kyodo News report.
</P>
<P>
The 47-ton girder fell some 60 meters onto the workers shortly
after noon after a wire on a crane snapped, the report said.
</P>
</TEXT>
