<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Presidents Delivers Speech in Beijing University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In his address at Beijing University, President Scalfaro
described the role of China as "extremely important".
</P>
<P>
He said Italy is ready to conduct closer dialogues, wider
economic cooperation and cultural exchanges that comply with
traditions of both countries, as well as collaborations in
science, technology, art and sports with China.
</P>
<P>
President Scalfaro told some 500 students and faculty members
present that Italy has taken notice of China's responsibility in
dealing with the financial crisis that swepted major countries in
Asia and positively appraises its role in the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Italy is convinced that China would continue to contribute to
the United Nations' reform of improving its efficiency,
representativeness and democracy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, President Scalfaro recalled the longstanding history
of bilateral exchanges between Italy and China in his speech and
elaborated his views on peace, state-to-state relations and human
rights.
</P>
<P>
President Scalfaro will also travel to the cities of Xi'an and
Shanghai besides Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
