<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
dropped for the 10th consecutive day Wednesday as worries over an
endless plunge of the New Zealand dollar hit the sentiment, and
sharply higher short-term interest rates also affected yield
stocks.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index slumped 31 points to end at 2,067 with a
turnover of nearly 112 million New Zealand dollars (55 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the main leaders, Air New Zealand eased 3 cents to 189
cents. Brierley Investment rose 7 cents to 98 cents. Carter Holt
Harvey lost 7 cents to 197 cents. Fletcher Energy slumped 38 cents
to 480 cents. Fletcher Building dived 24 cents to 270 cents. Lion
Nathan remained stable at 430 cents. Telecom fell 14 cents to 825
cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 28 rises and 75 falls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
