<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets With Mauritanian Army Chief of Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Defense Minister Chi Haotian, in
a meeting with the Chief of Staff of the Mauritanian National
Army, Moulaye Boukhreiss, here today, said that although their two
countries are distant from each other, they are related because of
similar historical events and common tasks like maintaining world
peace and development.
</P>
<P>
He said that since Sino-Mauritanian diplomatic relations were
established, the two countries have developed a good relationship
in many areas like international affairs.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government appreciates Boukhreiss' visit, Chi said,
and he believes that it will push bilateral relations to a new
level.
</P>
<P>
Boukhreiss expressed his excitement over being the first
Mauritanian Army chief of staff to visit China abd said he hopes
that cooperation between the two armies will increase along with
cooperative relations in all other fields. 
