<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Air France, Striking Pilots Reach Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The management of Air France and
striking pilots Wednesday reached an agreement to end a 10-day
strike, just hours before the Football World Cup begins in France.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the SNPL, which is the main pilots
union involved in the strike, has called on its members to go back
to work as soon as possible, said the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The strike began on June 1 as the pilots were opposed to the
air company's plan to reduce their salaries by 15 percent in
exchange for its shares.
</P>
<P>
The strikers also wanted the scrapping of a double system in
pays between older and younger pilots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
