<HEADLINE> Number of AIDS Orphans Rises in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The number of children orphaned
by AIDS in Kenya is expected to reach 600,000 by 2000, local
press reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Greg Owino, the information and communication officer at the
country office of the U.N. Children's Fund, Tuesday described the
impact of HIV/AIDS on Kenyan children as "catastrophic."
</P>
<P>
He noted that out of the 1.3 million Kenyans infected with HIV
this year, 77,950 are children.
</P>
<P>
The situation is as "a landmine which is about to explode," he
warned, calling for urgent efforts against the spreading of the
fatal disease.
</P>
<P>
Greg Owino made the remarks at the launch of a week-long
celebrations towards the Day of the African Child set for June
16.  
</P>
