<HEADLINE> Beijing Increasing Workers' Salaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Beijing will raise the minimum of
workers salaries from July 1, with the approval of the municipal
government.
</P>
<P>
Relief funds for unemployed workers, minimum stipend for
laid-off workers, and old-age pensions will also be raised,
according to the Beijing Economic Daily Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The paper reported that the minimum wage will go from 1.7 yuan
per hour and 290 yuan per month to 1.8 yuan per hour and 310 yuan
monthly. Minimum monthly relief funds for unemployed people will
go from between 203 yuan and 247 yuan to 217 yuan to 264 yuan
monthly.
</P>
<P>
The minimum stipend for laid-off workers will go from 200 yuan
to 210 per month, and pensions for retired workers will go up by
50 yuan monthly. 
</P>
