<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number Of Rail Passengers In China Up Slightly In May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- China's railways carried 2.42
million passengers daily in May on average, a 0.1 percent increase
on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
The number of people travelling more than 500 kilometers in a
single trip was 595,000, a rise of 0.5 percent, according to the
Railway Ministry.
</P>
<P>
China's trains carried 270,000 TEUs (twenty-foot equivalent
units), 2.3 million tons of containers, increases of 1.9 percent
and 4.8 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Railway delivered 77,800 cars per day, 1,400 cars more than
their target. Key materials like oil, minerals, metals, cement,
timber, and chemical fertilizers were all above their monthly
targets, but coal was down 400 cars to 28,890 cars per day.
</P>
<P>
Railway departments have taken steps to improve service and
increase the speed of trains since April 1997, to deal with the
challenge from highway and air transport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
