<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese City Developing High-tech Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The city of Zhuhai in China's
Guangdong Province has 37,500 people working in high-tech
industries, producing 390,000 yuan per capita in output value.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, the sector has done well in this Special Economic
Zone, especially electronic information, biotechnology, new
materials, and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Zhuhai had an output value of 12 billion yuan from
high-tech products, accounting for 25.9 percent of the city's
total industrial output value. It now has 38 high-tech
enterprises, with output worth 1.92 billion yuan, profits of 417
million yuan, and 26.6 million yuan in exports in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai's High-tech Development Zone had revenues of 2.1 billion
yuan in 1997, industrial output of 1.8 billion yuan, and 30
million US dollars worth of exports.
</P>
<P>
It has also increased technology and trade co-operation with
the United States, Canada, Australia, and east Asian countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
