<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Kenyan Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Kenyan newspapers Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Times:
</P>
<P>
-- The International Monetary Fund demands an explanation for
the excessive interest allegedly accrued by Kenya's domestic debt
which overshot projected estimates four years ago, a Nairobi
court heard Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Daily Nation:
</P>
<P>
-- Burundian army said Tuesday that it killed 13 Hutu rebels
and lost one soldier in a weekend clash.
</P>
<P>
-- African leaders Tuesday debated sending a peace mission to
the Horn of Africa where Ethiopia and Eritrea showed no signs of
abandoning their deadly border dispute.
</P>
<P>
East African Standard:
</P>
<P>
-- Kenyan Finance Minister Simeon Nyachae will present
Thursday what is widely expected to be an austerity budget,
needed to get the economy out of a recession. 
</P>
</TEXT>
