<HEADLINE> Vandals Puncture Bulgarian Oil Pipeline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOURGAS, Bulgaria, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Vandals are believed to
have been responsible for rupturing a pipeline which spilled crude
oil into a tailings pond near Bourgas in Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
The oil was discovered Tuesday morning, spouting from a
pipeline linking the oil port and a refinery, in the 24th such
incident this year, said police.
</P>
<P>
The spill measured 200 meters in length and crude oil was
running off into marshy terrain a few hundred meters from the sea,
the Civil Defense organization said.
</P>
<P>
The Civil Defense and Neftochim special units took emergency
measures to prevent oil from reaching the sea and the nearby
Mandrensko Lake. The clean-up operation is still underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
