<HEADLINE> Slovakia Opens Its Second Nuclear Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia's second nuclear power
station went into operation on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Construction on the Mochovce nuclear power plant, with a total
investment of 60 billion korun (1.88 billion U.S. dollars),
started in 1981.
</P>
<P>
The plant, equipped with four Russian-made VVER-440 light-water
reactors, has a total capacity of 1.76 million kilowatts.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia generates 50 percent of its electricity from nuclear
energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
