<DOCNO> XIE19980610.0303 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cancer Rate on Rise in Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The incidence of cancer has doubled
in the past 15 years in Bulgaria, with a total of 26,000 cases of
malignant tumors diagnosed each year.
</P>
<P>
About 3,000 are women diagnosed with breast cancer, an average
of nine each day in a country of around 8.4 million, said
Associate Professor Samuel Danon, head of National Register for
Cancer Diseases, as he commented on the results of a research
program, Data on Breast Cancer Prophylaxis, in Veliko Turnovo,
northern Bulgaria, Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics put the number of patients hospitalized with
cancer at 180,000 in Bulgaria, Danon said.
</P>
<P>
Half of the women diagnosed with breast cancer die due to
belated diagnosis. Only 63 percent of breast cancer cases are
diagnosed in the initial stages, he said.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that more than one million women throughout the
world die of breast cancer a year.
</P>
<P>
Prophylactic examinations and free consultations for women from
Veliko Turnovo are planned for the next three weeks. Breast cancer
prophylaxis is part a program on healthy living which is operating
for a third consecutive year in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
