<HEADLINE> Two World Best Marks Set in Grand Prix Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Two Kenyan runners set a pair of
world best marks this year on Tuesday at the Slovnaft Grand Prix
Track meet in Bratislava, Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 3,000 steeplechase, Joseph Keter became the
fastest athlete this year after clocking 8 minutes, 8.91 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Jackline Marange set another best mark this year in the world
in the women's 1,500 meters with a 4:00.81 clocking.
</P>
<P>
American Mark Crear won the men's 110-meter hurdles with a
time of 13.13 seconds, just missing the world best by 0.1
second.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Natalya Sadova won the women's discuss, beating
Anastasia Kelesidou of Greece and world champion Beatrice
Faumine of New Zeland into second and third places. 
</P>
