<HEADLINE> Northern Chinese Coal Center Wants To Be Leading Power Source </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Shanxi Province, China's major
coal producer, is working on becoming the country's largest
electricity provider.
</P>
<P>
According to a three-year plan, the provincial government will
set aside 70 billion yuan for improving 10 large power plants.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the Yangcheng Power Plant, which cost 13.2
billion yuan, is nearing completion. The first generating unit is
expected to provide electricity for Jiangsu Province by 2000 and
work on two other power plants to provide electricity for Shandong
Province and Tianjin Municipality will start soon.
</P>
<P>
When these are completed, Shanxi will have an installed
capacity of 6.5 million kws, and be able to produce 30 billion kwh
of electricity for other Chinese provinces annually.  
</P>
