<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Tamil Rebels Attack Rival Party MP's House </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A group of rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) Tuesday mounted a fierce
attack on the residence of district member of Parliament
Vaithiyalingam Balachandran in Vavuniya in Northern province.
</P>
<P>
Balachandran belongs to the Peoples Liberation Organization of
Tamil Eelam (PLOTE), a party now in the mainstream of politics and
a rival to the LTTE, reports reaching here from the north said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In the attack, a police sentry on duty was killed. Balachandran
was at home at the time of the raid but escaped unhurt through the
back door with his wife, five children and his mother.
</P>
<P>
The rebels, who had arrived in a hijacked vehicle, used
automatic weapons and rocket propelled grenades in the attack.
Extensive damage was caused to the MP's house. The rebels also
removed the MP's vehicle which was later found abandoned a few
miles away.
</P>
<P>
The reports said that a joint police-army operation has been
launched to trace the attackers.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a war against the government for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country since
1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
