<HEADLINE> Hingis Qualified for Season-ending Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Women's world number one Martina
Hingis of Switzerland has qualified for the WTA Tour's
season-ending Chase Championships.
</P>
<P>
In winning her quarter-final match with Venus Williams of the
United States at the French Open last week, Hingis has accumulated
enough points in 1998 to secure a place in the elite 16-player
field for the third consecutive year, no matter what she does the
rest of the season.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old Australian Open champion earned a berth in
the prestigious season finale after just 23 weeks of
competition in 1998, becoming the fastest qualifier in the
history of the championships.
</P>
<P>
The million U.S. dollars Chase Championships will be held at
New York's Madison Square Garden November 16-22. 
