<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto
Robaina and his visiting Italian counterpart, Lamberto Dini,
signed a cooperation agreement on Tuesday on combating criminal
activities.
</P>
<P>
This was part of a series of agreements signed between the two
nations recently, covering cooperation in investment, culture and
fighting drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Dini described the crime agreement as one of utmost social and
political importance.
</P>
<P>
Before signing the agreement, the two ministers met and
exchanged views on relations between countries in Europe and Latin
America and the Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
Dini arrived here Monday night for an official visit. He is
the first Italian foreign minister to visit Cuba and the first
high-ranking official from the European Union to go to the
Caribbean island in recent years.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Dini is also expected to meet Cuban Vice
President Carlos Lage and Parliamentary Speaker Ricardo Alarcon.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the trade volume between Cuba and Italy reached more
than 150 million U.S. dollars. More than 200,000 tourists from
Italy visited Cuba. 
