<HEADLINE> Car Sales Down Sharply in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The number of passenger cars sold
in May 1998 dropped by a very high 55.3 percent from 6,603 units a
year ago to only 2,951 units, according to the latest statistics
from the Chamber of Automotive Manufacturers of the Philippines
Inc.
</P>
<P>
In a report published Wednesday, the chamber said car sales
have been on the downtrend for the past year and was aggravated by
the currency crisis.
</P>
<P>
The statistics showed that for the first five months total
sales reached 17,111, down 50 percent from 33,912 units sold in
the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
On a month-on-month basis, sales in May saw another 4 percent
decline from April sales of 3,075 units.
</P>
<P>
The chamber said passenger car sales continued to be adversely
affected by higher prices due to the devalued peso, increased
financing charges and slow and selective approval of retail
financing applications.
</P>
<P>
Honda Cars Philippines Inc. regained its leadership in the
passenger car market in May, with its sales reaching a hefty 1,190
units during the month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
