<HEADLINE> Helping The Needy In Northwest China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- China's Shaanxi Province will move
its people living in poverty in three years to give them better
living conditions, provincial government sources say.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi still has nearly 2 million people living below the
poverty line, a quarter of a million of them with special
difficulties because of geographical conditions.
</P>
<P>
The local government had made an effort to help the extremely
poor in recent years, but many of them suffering from disease and
other troubles still have food and clothing problems. So the
government has decided to move them to better places.
</P>
<P>
Farmers will be allowed to decide whether or not to move, or
they can move elsewhere but return to their original place within
three years. The government will also sign contracts with farmers
to safeguard their rights.
</P>
<P>
The resettlement program, which has already been used on a
trial basis, has been successful in helping more than 20,000
people, so the province plans to resettle another 70,000 this year.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wei, Shaanxi's deputy governor, has also signed
responsibility agreements with local officials to insure success
of the program.
</P>
<P>
Neighboring Gansu Province and Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region
have given at least 700,000 people a better living standard
through similar efforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
