<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Teachers Strike Over Payment Row </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- About 160,000 public school
teachers in Venezuela started a 48-hour strike on Tuesday after
the Education Ministry failed to settle a payment debt with their
union.
</P>
<P>
The Teachers Association said the government owed 150 billion
bolivars (278 million U.S. dollars) to public school teachers,
including bonus back pay and geographic benefits for those working
in remote areas.
</P>
<P>
The Education Ministry acknowledged a debt of only 29 billion
bolivars (54 million dollars) and said it would settle the debt in
July.
</P>
<P>
The strike will leave four million students in public schools
across the country without classes for two days. 
</P>
