<HEADLINE> Berasategui Retires Injured at Bologna Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Alberto Berasategui of Spain,
carrying an injury from the recent French Open, retired hurt
during his first round against Argentine Hernan Gumy at the men's
tennis tournament in Bologna on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Berasategui quit the tournament he won two years ago at 3-0
down to Gumy in the deciding set.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Julian Alonso became the tournament's highest ranked
survivor after defeating fellow Spaniard Pepe Imaz 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Costa of Spain, 5th seed, beat german Marcello Craca
6-4, 6-4 while 6th seeded Karim Alami of Morocco edged david
Sanchez of Spain 6-4, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
