<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina, Brazil Jointly Condemn Nuclear Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The governments of Argentina
and Brazil reiterated their "regret and shock" over repeated
nuclear tests by India and Pakistan last month in a joint statment
issued here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a press release distributed by the Argentine Foreign
Ministry, the two governments also reaffirmed their commitments to
non-proliferation of nuclear weapons.
</P>
<P>
They said that renouncing the development and possession of
nuclear weapons is the best way to ensure regional and global
peace and security.
</P>
<P>
They stated that the huge resources and time spent in
developing weapons of mass destruction do not contribute at all to
overcoming the adverse conditions and extreme poverty which still
scourge many countries.
</P>
<P>
The governments of Brazil and Argentina urged the international
community and all countries to adopt urgent measures to eliminate
nuclear weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
