<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Baoshan Iron, Steel Group Exports Drill Rods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- The Steel Tube Company of Baoshan
Iron and Steel Group has received orders from Trans-Texas Gas
Company of the United States for making 500 tons of drill rods for
the latter company.
</P>
<P>
The rods will soon be shipped to the U.S. soon. It is the first
time for the Shanghai-based company to export drill rods to the
United States, said a company executive.
</P>
<P>
Before this, the Shanghai company shipped 250 tons of drill
rods (type G-105) to the United States, which had been used by the
U.S. company to drill a 5,091.16-m-deep oil well in Houston, said
Alan Drane, deputy general manager of the U.S. company, in a
letter to the Shanghai company. 
