<HEADLINE> Southern African Sports Meeting Ends in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A two-day meeting of the Southern
African Regional Police Chiefs Cooperation Organisation (SARPCCO)
sports co-ordinators ended in Harare on Tuesday with a
recommendation to have annual sports and regional competitions in
soccer, netball, volleyball, darts and athletics on a rotational
basis.
</P>
<P>
The police sports co-ordinators from Botswana, Namibia,
Swaziland, Lesotho, South Africa, Tanzania and Zimbabwe attended
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
"the south African representatives indicated their willingness
to host the inaugural competition," a statement released at the
end of the meeting said.
</P>
<P>
"the tentative dates for the inaugural sports meeting are
September 27 to October 3 1998," the statement added.
</P>
<P>
The meeting sought to promote, strengthen and perpetuate
cooperation and foster joint strategies for the management of all
forms of cross-border and related crimes with regional
implications through sport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
