<HEADLINE> British Driver Mcrae Wins 45th Acropolis Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 9 (Xinhhua) -- British driver Colin Mcrae Tuesday
won the 45th International Rally Acropolis which began Sunday
morning with the participation of 103 cars.
</P>
<P>
It is the British driver's second win at the international car
competition. In 1996, he had won the 43rd Acropolis rally.
</P>
<P>
Second was France's Didier Auriol, who clocked in 20 seconds
behind Mcrae. Finnish driver Juha Kankkunen came in third while
the leading Greek driver was Leonidas Kirkos in eighth place.
</P>
<P>
The participating cars covered an overall distance of 1031.97
kilometers over the three days, which included 17 special sections
totaling 388.76 kilometers. 
</P>
