<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southeast Asian Countries Favored By Beijing Holiday-makers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Taking advantage of the
depreciated currencies in southeast Asia, residents in the Chinese
capital city Beijing have made southeast Asian countries their
tourist destinations.
</P>
<P>
According to Beijing tourism administration, over 50,000 people
in Beijing traveled abroad for holidays between August last year
and February this year and most of them went sightseeing in
Thailand, Malaysia, Macao and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Five international travel agencies in Beijing began to handle
international travel business last August. By the end of April,
they had used up the annual quotas granted by the state tourism
administration, local sources said.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there is still control over citizens' travelling
abroad. The official tourism destinations are limited at
Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand, Philippines, in addition to Hong
Kong and Macao. 
</P>
