<HEADLINE> Anhui Keen to Develop Service Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province will make
greater efforts to develop the service sector to make it a major
driving force for local economic growth, according to the
provincial planning commission.
</P>
<P>
The output value of Anhui's service sector will be raised to
117 billion yuan before the year 2000, up from 48.4 billion yuan
in 1984, the commission said.
</P>
<P>
It also said that the payroll of the service sector will rise
to 10 million people from 7.2 million people in 1995 and the
proportion of the sector in the provincial gross domestic product
will increase from 24.1 percent to 32 percent during the period.
</P>
<P>
To these ends, Anhui will seek to establish a unified, open,
and orderly competitive market system characterized by standard
management and adequate supervision.
</P>
<P>
Priority will be given to the development of catering trade,
transportation, postal services, banking, insurance, tourism and
real estate, according to the commission.
</P>
<P>
Anhui will build one to two specialized wholesale markets
valued at 1 billion yuan or more each and a dozen smaller ones
in the next one or two years, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
