<HEADLINE> Chile: Satisfied with Blatter's reelection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, June 9 (Xinhua) -- In regard to the election of
Joseph Blatter as the new FIFA president, Ricardo Abumohor,
president of the Chilean National Association of Professional
Football (ANFP) declared "a task which has correctly undertaken
for years finally resulted victorious".
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Brazilian press from Paris (which was
published today), the head of the ANFP declared that Blatter was
"an expert in what has been done in the past and in the plans for
the future".
</P>
<P>
"One shouldn't think that the Latin-American football has been
successful, but a whole labor and several achievements", he said.
</P>
<P>
Abumohor continued: "I don't believe that in the case of
Johansson success, he would have liked to damage us, as part of
his program, what happens is that we feel closer to Blatter, we
already know him, he is acquainted with us and understands our
virtues and defects".
</P>
<P>
When Abuhomor was asked about the specific effect that the
promotion of Blatter to the top position of the worldwide football
should have in the Chilean population, Abumohor replied "There is
not any project in particular that has to do with his promotion,
but I can tell that the development of the Chilean football will
be maintained, and that the good image he has demonstrated at an
international level will not be changed".
</P>
<P>
In regards to Blatter's victory assuring the four positions for
South America in the next football world championship he said: "I
believe that South America has the four positions already and the
preliminary rounds will be done among everybody; there is already
a principle of agreement." 
</P>
