<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui Successfully Implements Re-employment Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
taken effective measures to help displaced workers find new jobs
this year, according the provincial federation of trade unions.
</P>
<P>
Some 60 percent of the laid-off workers in Anhui have been
re-employed this year in addition to 150,000 new workers, with the
province's official unemployment rate controlled around the
targeted 3.5 percent level.
</P>
<P>
One of the measures to ensure re-employment of the displaced
workers is the introduction of a responsibility system among
governments at all levels.
</P>
<P>
The provincial authorities have also mobilized the higher
education institutions and professionals and vocational schools to
launch various training programs.
</P>
<P>
By the end of April, Anhui has raised 87 million yuan for the
local re-employment project. The funds have benefited 270,000
laid-off workers, or 60 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
As China's moves to a market economy, more and more workers
have been laid off by the state-owned enterprises, which used to
be highly overstaffed and economically inefficient.
</P>
<P>
To counter increasing unemployment and help the displaced
workers, China has launched a national re-employment project to
train and divert such workers, mainly to the service sector.
</P>
</TEXT>
