<HEADLINE> Shanghai Building Second Passenger Railway Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest
industrial city, kicked off the construction a new passenger
railway station Monday.
</P>
<P>
The station, the second in this largest economic and financial
center of China, has 13 pairs of tracks, six platforms, two
passenger passages, a package tunnel and other facilities.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the railway station's first phase, which
includes seven pairs of tracks and three platforms, will be
completed before October next year.
</P>
<P>
The new station will be linked with the city's subway system
and will be mainly used for southbound passenger trains leaving for
the suburban areas and Hangzhou, capital of neighboring Zhejiang
Province. 
</P>
