<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Major market indexes on the New
York Stock Exchange posted mixed performance Friday in another
hesitant session before Wednesday's congressional report by
Federal Reserve chairman Alan Greenspan.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 19.68 points to 9,049.92.
The loss ended a three-session, 265-point climb back toward May
13's record of 9,211.84.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indexes rose, led by the technology-heavy Nasdaq
composite, but declining issues outnumbered advancers overall.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 rose 2.71 to 1,118.43, and the
technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 12.99 to 1,800.76.
</P>
<P>
Decliners outnumbered advancers by a 9-to-7 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 560.56 million shares,
up from 533.68 million on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 0.68 to 577.50, and the American
Stock Exchange composite index rose 0.38 to 714.07.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 0.40 to
456.74.
</P>
<P>
With no major economic reports due until later in the week,
analysts will be looking for clues as to whether Fed officials
might raise the central bank's key lending rates to keep inflation
in check by slowing the economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
