<HEADLINE> Nigeria Appeals for Int'l Understanding, Coop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's new leader General
Abdusalam Abubakar has appealed to the international community
for understanding of and cooperation with his government.
</P>
<P>
In a national broadcast at 9:00 p.m. Tuesday at the State
Nigerian TV Authority, Ababukar said that Nigeria demands fair
hearing and constructive engagement, not isolation.
</P>
<P>
He said Nigeria remains an important member of the
international system through the framework of the United Nations,
an important instrument of international cooperation and
interdependence.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar, who assumed the leadership of Nigeria early Tuesday
morning, said Nigeria shall honor all its international
obligations, and maintains its commitment to international peace
and security, especially in the west African sub-region.
</P>
<P>
He said that Nigeria intends to develop its relations with all
the nations in the world, but in view of the recent development
in the country, Nigeria will resolutely defends its sovereignty,
independence and territory integrity.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar was named Nigeria's new leader by the highest ruling
body, the provisional ruling council, after the death of former
head of state, General Sani Abacha Monday morning in Abuja, as a
result of a heart attack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
