<HEADLINE> Britain's Special Envoy for Cyprus Visits Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Britain's special envoy for Cyprus,
Sir David Hannay, Tuesday discussed with Greek Foreign
Undersecretary Yiannos Kranidiotis the Cyprus problem,
Euro-Turkish relations and the priorities of Britain's European
Union rotating presidency.
</P>
<P>
Hannay, who is in Athens as part of Britain's preparatory
consultations with EU members in view of the forthcoming Cardiff
summit.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Hannay said that his country hoped to see an
improved version of December's Luxemburg summit decisions
concerning Euro-Turkish ties at the Cardiff summit, the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The British official also stressed that London was in favor of
the unblocking of EU funds for Turkey, which Greece has rejected
for Ankara's bad relations with Athens.  
</P>
</TEXT>
