<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Abubakar Appeals to Nigerian Exiles to Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's new leader General
Abdusalam Abubakar has appealed to self-exiled Nigerians to
return home and join the continued implementation of the
transition program.
</P>
<P>
In a broadcast at 9:00 p.m. Tuesday at the State Nigerian TV
Authority, Abubakar said his government needs the cooperation of
all well-meaning Nigerians in its efforts to continue the
transition to civil rule program of late head of state General
Sani Abacha who reportedly died Monday of a heart attack.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar urged the exiles to return and join the
reconstruction, reconciliation and concluding of the transition
program.
</P>
<P>
In his first public declaration of major policies, Abubakar
said his government remains fully committed to the social and
political transitio program of Abacha's administration.
</P>
<P>
He said his government will do everything possible to ensure
its full and successful implementation.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar, who assumed the leadership of Nigeria early Tuesday
morning, said he is now holding consultations with all relevant
agencies at the highest level.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar also announced a national mourning period from June 9
to July 7 in honor of Abacha, who was buried late Monday in his
home town in Kano City in northern Nigeria, according to Islamic
traditions.
</P>
<P>
He announced that condolence registers will be opened in
strategic places in Federal Capital Abuja, state capitals and
local government headquarters throughout the nation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
